Package: needy
Type: Package
Title: needy
Description: needy is a small utility library designed to make testing function inputs less difficult.R is a dynamically typed language, but larger projects need some degree of input validation for scalabity. needy offers a single function, needs_a( ), which lets you specify the traits an object should have, such as class, size, numerical properties or number of parameters.
Version: 0.1
Depends:
    R (>= 2.14.0)
Date: 2013-02-03
Author: Ryan Grannell
Maintainer: Ryan Grannell <r.grannell2@gmail.com>
